Revolutionary Innovative Intelligentsia

We aim to be a think tank and community for people who want to create new ideas online and offline for improving the world! From small to big ideas. We have just set up our first few steps towards it on the Grid and we will work our asses off to create a leap board for new ideas to be put in system.

item.title: The Grid Support Blog
item.description:
The Grid Support Blog

The Grid isn't an option for sharing by default. This video will show you how to enable it, and then share a photo to The Grid. After you enable sharing, you can also share content from your browser.

item.title: SFCandyBar
item.description:
SFCandyBar

Amy Rose, San Francisco, CA SF Candy Bar made my guests feel like kids in a candy shop, while creating a beautiful and sophisticated look customized to my colors and my sweet tooth. The Candy Bar was a social and conversational centerpiece providing a unique and personalized flair for my special night.

item.title: Joseph Jewell Wines
item.description:
Joseph Jewell Wines

This Joseph Jewell Pinot is joyous in fresh berry fruit aromas and flavors, from wild strawberry to taut cherry, the fruit buoyed by lush, velvety tannins and generous acidity. Pretty on the nose and tongue, it discloses a trace of vanilla on the clean, distinct finish...Buy this wine
